Our Wilora Hawthorne Shaker Espresso collection feature a natural wood look, with deep, warm tones for classic kitchens. Colors: Cinder, Espresso, dark grey, dark wood\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoor Frames: Raised or recessed frames, or frameless slab-style\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eHardware: Contrasting colors and lighter metals like chrome or nickel\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMolding and Panels: Any\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nWhat are Kitchen Cabinets Made Of?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhether you choose to go with framed or frameless cabinets, the various components are made from different materials. At Vevano, our cabinets are durable and have plenty of character.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBox Material\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe storage area is the cabinet box. Some manufacturers use particleboard because it\u0026rsquo;

4546s an affordable material. However, particleboard isn\u0026rsquo;

4547t made to last and tends to sag and warp under the weight of heavy dishes and marble countertops. As such, we use plywood because it\u0026rsquo;

4548s durable, sturdy, and lasts much longer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur framed cabinets use plywood boards with a UV-coated wood-veneered interior. Every time you open your cabinets, you show off a natural woodgrain finish, adding to the overall style.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOur frameless cabinets use plywood with a white-grey linen interior infused with a durable thermofused melamine surface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFramed Door Materials\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith shaker, raised, or recessed cabinets in our framed cabinet collections, the door and drawer fronts are made of five pieces \u0026ndash;

4549 a four-piece frame with a center panel.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor stained cabinets, the four-piece frame is made of solid birch with a veneered MDF (medium-density fiberboard) center panel. However, our Wilora Hawthorne Wildwood Saddle cabinets are made entirely of solid birch.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor painted cabinets, the frame and center panel are made of HDF (high-density fiberboard) for stability and durability. Since HDF doesn\u0026rsquo;

4550t expand and contract like wood, it\u0026rsquo;

4551s ideal for a framed door because the seams aren\u0026rsquo;

4552t as likely to separate.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrameless Door Material\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe frameless doors in the Wilora Paloma collection are made from engineered wood with textured melamine surfaces. The single-piece slab style doors are great for engineered wood as the wood is free to expand or contract without fear of separating seams.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nPros and Cons of Kitchen Cabinet Materials\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSolid Birch \u0026ndash;

4553 \u003c/strong\u003ea solid board harvested from a birch tree. Commonly used for cabinets and furniture because it\u0026rsquo;

4554s widely available and durable.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eReal wood with unique grain patterns\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEasy to stain\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eCan be refinished\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eExpands and contracts with moisture and humidity\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMore expensive than engineered wood or fiberboard\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eSusceptible to bug infestation and rot\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eEngineered Wood with a Thermofused Melamine Surface \u0026ndash;

4555 \u003c/strong\u003ea slab made of several layers of sliced wood glued and pressed together with heat to create a board with a wood-grain textured surface.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMore affordable than solid wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoesn\u0026rsquo;

4556t expand and warp to changes in humidity\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLower quality wood material\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eCan\u0026rsquo;

4557t be refinished\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eUses potentially harmful adhesives\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eHDF (high-density fiberboard) \u0026ndash;

4558 \u003c/strong\u003ea board made of wood fibers mixed with glues and resins and pressed together under pressure to create a dense material used for cabinet panels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTakes a consistent coat of paint very well\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eExtremely hard\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eStable in humid and dry environments\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoesn\u0026rsquo;

4559t have a wood grain\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eWarps and swells when exposed to water\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLacks the lifespan of wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eMDF (medium-density fiberboard) \u0026ndash;

4560 \u003c/strong\u003ea board made in similar fashion to HDF, but without as much pressure, making it lighter and less dense. Used primarily for panels.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEasy to paint\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLightweight\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eAffordable\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eNot as durable as HDF\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eWarps and swells when wet\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eShort shelf life in comparison to other materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003ePlywood \u0026ndash;

4561 \u003c/strong\u003ethinly sliced sheets of wood glued and pressed together while alternating woodgrain direction 90 degrees. Used for cabinet boxes, shelves, and drawer floors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eDoesn\u0026rsquo;

4562t warp or swell in high humidity\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eStable and strong enough hold heavy items\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTakes a veneer, making it easy to get a beautiful wood look without the cost\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMore expensive than other engineered materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eNot as strong as solid wood\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLow-quality plywood comes apart too easily\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eParticleboard \u0026ndash;

4563\u003c/strong\u003e a board made of sawdust, wood chips, synthetic resins and glues pressed together under heat.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePros:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eExtremely budget friendly\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLightweight and great for drawer boxes\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eUses wood by-product and recycled materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCons:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLeast durable wood product for cabinetry\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eSags under heavy dishes, countertops, or appliances\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eEasily chipped or broken\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nHow to Install Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHiring a professional to install your kitchen cabinets is costly. You can expect to pay between $150 to $500 per cabinet or $150 to $350 per square foot. However, you don\u0026rsquo;

4564t have to spend anything. While installing cabinets takes time and sweat, it isn\u0026rsquo;

4565t overly complicated. With the right equipment, precise measurements, and a little confidence you can install your own kitchen cabinets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTake very detailed measurements of your kitchen.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFind and mark wall studs with a pencil or chalk.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMark lines to indicate where the top base cabinets will go. Typically, the top of the base cabinet is 34 \u0026frac12;

4566\u0026rdquo;

4567 above the floor, but it can vary with desk base cabinets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eMark another line at about 53 7/8\u0026rdquo;

4568 above the floor to indicate where the bottom of the wall cabinets will be.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFinally, mark a top line to indicate the top of the cabinets at between 83 7/8\u0026rdquo;

4569 \u0026ndash;

4570 95 7/8\u0026rdquo;

4571 (depending on the height of your wall cabinets). (Check the design plan you received from your designer for specific measurements and a more detailed install guide.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eStarting with your corner wall cabinet box (without the door), use a power drill and a screw (never a nail) to secure the box to the wall by drilling through the cabinet\u0026rsquo;

4572s back panel and into the studs. Make sure to do this at the top and bottom of the cabinet. Drill into two studs where possible. (Reference your design plan for measurements, especially for blind corner cabinets, which need a few inches of space between side walls.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eWhen installing the next wall cabinet, attach the side adjacent to the mounted cabinet by clamping the sides together and screwing the two cabinet sides together.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eNext, install base cabinets by starting with the corner cabinet, referring to your design packet for specific measurements.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eRepeat steps 6 and 7, secure the base cabinet to the wall studs and adjacent cabinets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWant to install your own kitchen cabinets? Contact our design team for a custom design plan. If you\u0026rsquo;

4573re hesitant about installing your own cabinets, we recommend hiring a professional installer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nCan I Paint Kitchen Cabinets?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYes, painting cabinets is a budget-friendly way to change the look and style of a kitchen without the cost of replacing everything. However, DIY kitchen cabinet painting is time-consuming and can get complex. The current state of your existing cabinets influences how easy your project will be.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, the surfaces of engineered wood, MDF, or HDF cabinets can\u0026rsquo;

4574t be refinished and prepped for a new coat of paint. They require you to paint over the old color, which may not take the new paint as consistently, causing pooled areas, dripping, and inconsistent streaking.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSolid wood cabinets, however, are easy to sand and prime for a smoother painting surface. But prepping the surface is a lot of time-consuming, physical work. If the surface is painted, you need to remove the paint and sand the surface. If the surface is stained, you need to sand the surface until the stain is gone.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026rsquo;

4575re looking for an easier solution to painting your cabinets, talk to one of our designers for free about a budget solution to update your kitchen. Vevano carries a wide variety of cabinet paint colors and stain styles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nChoosing the Perfect Kitchen Cabinet Hardware and Accessories\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eChanging up your kitchen accessories is a budget-friendly way to add style and function. Hardware is easy to update with changing styles and adds character to your cabinets. You can also use molding and cabinet lighting to give your cabinets a new look.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Hardware\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePulls and knobs cap off the style you\u0026rsquo;

4576re searching for while also providing functionality to your doors and drawers. The style of a pull helps determine if a shaker cabinet is either modern, classic, or farmhouse.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKnobs are smaller than pulls, typically designed for the fingertips. They come in a variety of sizes, shapes, materials, and finishes. Glass, crystal, metal, or ceramic knobs are all options, depending on the style you\u0026rsquo;

4577re looking for. Shapes are most often round or square but can be oval, geometric, birdcage, abstract, or more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePulls, on the other hand, are made to fit into your hand, providing greater leverage when opening and closing. This makes pulls ideal for heavy drawers and large doors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDrawer pulls are usually longer than knobs. And while the shape is different, the materials, styles, and finishes are typically the same as knobs. In fact, most pulls have knobs in the same style, allowing you to easily mix and match pulls and knobs in your kitchen without having styles clash.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Lights\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdd functionality and ambiance with under-cabinet and in-cabinet lights. Under-cabinet lighting is a strip of lights or a puck installed to the underside of wall cabinets, illuminating the wall and countertop. This helps with food preparation, cooking, and cleaning. It also brightens up the kitchen since the areas under wall cabinets are generally shadowy and dark. If you have glass-front cabinets, adding in-cabinet lights creates a sophisticated look, like museum display cases, to highlight your favorite decorative dishware. They also make finding what you want easy and fast.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Molding\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdded to the tops and bottoms of cabinets, molding adds a bit of panache and helps make your cabinets look complete and cohesive. Here are some different types of molding:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eCrown molding\u003c/em\u003e encapsulates many types of molding, but it\u0026rsquo;

4578s a decorative piece installed to the top of the wall cabinets, either to make the cabinets look taller or create a decorative transition between the cabinets and the ceiling.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAngle Crown Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a decorative piece placed between the bottom of the wall cabinet and the wall, creating a nice angled transition from the cabinet to the wall.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eLight rail molding\u003c/em\u003e goes on the outside bottom of wall cabinets, adding decorative edges while concealing under-cabinet lights.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eToe-kick molding\u003c/em\u003e covers the space between the cabinets and the floor.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eScribe Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a small piece of wood used to cover inconsistencies, such as small gaps between two cabinets or where a cabinet meets a wall.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eShoe Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a rounded piece of wood used to cover inconsistencies between the toe-kick molding and the floor or the wall and the floor.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eApron Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a decorative piece of wood used as trim on the underside of wall cabinets or for windows near the cabinets. It\u0026rsquo;

4579s used to conceal joints.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eBatten Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a thin strip of wood used to cover seams between panels or cabinets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eRope Molding \u003c/em\u003eis a decorative piece of wood carved to look like rope. It\u0026rsquo;

4580s used to cover seams or add decorative details.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eKitchen Cabinet Panels\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKitchen cabinet panels are affixed to the exposed sides of cabinets, islands, and appliances to cover the exposed, unfinished sides of a cabinet box. Panels are available in decorative end panels, refrigerator end panels, dishwasher panels, and more. Designed to \u0026ldquo;

4581finish\u0026rdquo;

4582 unfinished cabinets, panels are necessary to ensure a consistent look throughout your cabinets.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nHow to Organize Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWith so many styles, configurations, and options available, it\u0026rsquo;

4583s easy to customize \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/cabinets-organization/\"\u003eyour cabinet organization\u003c/a\u003e to your lifestyle. Organization is key to making your cabinet storage practical.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eShelves\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhile most cabinets come with shelving, there are many additional \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/cabinets-kitchen-parts-and-accessories/\"\u003ecabinet parts\u003c/a\u003e for making your life easier.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eShelf organizers for pots, pans, and their matching lids.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFloating shelves for your most used items (bowls, mugs, etc.), on eye-level shelves.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eRollout shelves as a terrific alternative to traditional shelves, making it easier to access large items.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003ePulldown shelves for accessing high items, so you don\u0026rsquo;

4584t need a step ladder and can access items safely.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eLazy Susans\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA Lazy Susan is a swiveling shelf ideal for corner cabinets where accessing the space is awkward and difficult. Perfect for containers, pots and pans, Tupperware, or snacks, a Lazy Susan provides an easier way to reach for kitchen necessities because you can turn the Lazy Susan, bringing the items to the front.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWhen storing containers on Lazy Susans, store lids with them or on the same shelf. These shelves are also great for storing snacks like crackers, canned food, or healthy afterschool treats.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDrawers\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDrawer organizers provide a great solution for safely storing utensils, flatware, and dishware. Large drawers are designed to accommodate stacked plates, food storage containers, mixing bowls, and more to keep your countertops free from clutter.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eStore cooking utensils in drawers by type of cooking, for easy access. Drawers close to the stove are perfect for oven gloves or pot-stirring spoons. Island drawers are great for flatware, close to seating or dining areas.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSpice Racks\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eKeep herbs and spices arranged neatly with a spice rack. Vevano carries a variety of spice rack organizers. Choose a door-mounted spice rack for upper shelves to keep your spice shakers at eye-level. Pick a drawer organizer spice rack to easily customize any drawer and keep your spices within reach. Vevano also carries spice rack base cabinets \u0026ndash;

4585 slim 6\u0026rdquo;

4586 cabinets with rollout drawers to store spices.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTrash Can Pull-Outs\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMaximize your storage space with a pull-out trash can. Many pull-outs also work for recycling and compost bins, or for storing cleaning supplies. A pull-out trash can also free up floor space in your kitchen and keeps trash out of reach from pets and children.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nFAQs About Kitchen Cabinets\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDo you have a question about your kitchen cabinet remodel? White is the most reflective but colors like cream and light greys also reflect more light than darker colors.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCheck out our \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/white-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003ewhite kitchen cabinet collections\u003c/a\u003e for a bright kitchen, or our \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/page/gray-kitchen-cabinet-collections/\"\u003egrey kitchen cabinet collections\u003c/a\u003e for a slightly warmer kitchen.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhat is the best height for kitchen cabinets?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe standard height for base cabinets is 34 \u0026frac12;

4588\u0026rdquo;

4589 (without countertops). The bottom of your wall cabinets should be about 54\u0026rdquo;

4590 above the floor. These measurements leave enough space between your wall cabinets and your counter for appliances and cooking space. Wall cabinets themselves are typically between 30\u0026rdquo;

4591 and 42\u0026rdquo;

4592 high, depending on the design of your kitchen, the cabinet style, and height of your ceiling.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eWhen do you need a cabinet contractor?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHire a cabinet contractor when you\u0026rsquo;

We work with your contractor throughout the shipping, assembly, and installation process to ensure your overall satisfaction.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eWe recommend hiring a cabinet contractor if any of the following apply to you:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eYou don\u0026rsquo;

4594t have another person to help you.\u003c/em\u003e Wall cabinets require at least two people to safely and accurately install.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eYou\u0026rsquo;
